nal form of elative adjective while the measure for elative in Arabic is afa\'la. Shararun (pl. ashraar) - sparks of fire.',85,1559,'ROOT'),(746,'$rT','shrṭ','','','شرط','شرط',1,'To impose a condition. Ashraatun (pl. of shartun) - sign, token.',85,1567,'ROOT'),(747,'$rE','shr‘','','','شرع','شرع',5,'To be seated upon a road, open a street (door), establish a law, begin, appoint a religion. Shurra\'un (pl. of shaari\'un) - in shoals, upon shoals, breaking the water surface, holding up (their heads), appearing manifestly. Shir\'atun & shari\'atun - law or institution prescribed by God, right way or mode of action, clear highway/course/path.\r\n',85,1569,'ROOT'),(748,'$rq','shrq','shrq','','شرق','شرق',17,'To split, rise, slit. sharqiyyun - of or pertaining to the east, eastern. Mashriq - place of sunrise, east. mashriqain - two easts/horizons, two places where the sun rises (in winter and summer, East and West). Mashaariq - different points of sunrise, whence the sun rises in the course of the year, beam, gleam, eastern parts. Ashraqa (vb. 4) - to shine, rise. ishraaq - sunrise. Mushriqun - one on whom the sun has risen, who does anything at sunrise, one entering at the sunrise.',85,1574,'ROOT'),(749,'$rk','shrk','shrk','','شرك','شرك',168,'To be a companion, be sharer/partner. shirkun - share, participation, polytheism, idolatry, making associate/partner with Allah. Shariik (pl. shurakaa) - associate, partner, sharer. Nouns of the second declension when followed by the affixed pronouns take the three inflexions thus shurakaa, shurakaa\'i, shurakaa\'a. shaarak (vb. 3) - to share with. Ashraka (vb. 4) - to make a sharer or associate, give companions (e.g. to God), be a polytheist or idolater. ashraktumuuni - you associated me as partner. Mushrik - one who gives associate to God, polytheist. Mushtarikun (vb. 8) - one who partakes or shares.',86,1576,'ROOT'),(750,'$ry','shry','shry','','شري','شري',25,'To buy/sell/barter/purchase, conclude a sale, give or take in exchange, refuse, choose, prefer, give up anything and take another, lay hold on another.',86,1579,'ROOT'),(751,'$TA','shṭ\'','','','شطا','شطا',2,'To bring out the stalk (of a plant), sprout forth, walk on the bank of a river or valley. Shat\'un - the stalk of a plant. shaati\'un (pl. shawaatiun) - branch of or shoot of a river or valley.',86,1584,'ROOT'),(752,'$Tr','shṭr','','','شطر','شطر',5,'To part in two, divide into halves, the direction of, towards.',86,1585,'ROOT'),(753,'$TT','shṭṭ','','','شطط','شطط',3,'To be far off, wrong anyone, treat with injustice, go beyond due bounds. Shattan - extravagant lie, exceeding, redundant, excess. ashatta (vb. 4) - to act unjustly.',86,1583,'ROOT'),(754,'$Tn','shṭn','','','شطن','شطن',88,'(Root of shaytan) = become distant/far/remote, enter firmly / become firmly fixed therein / penetrate and be concealed, turn away in opposition (from direction/aim), devil, one excessively proud/corrupt, unbelieving/rebellious/insolent/audacious/obstinate/perverse, rope, deep curved well, it burned, became burnt, serpent, any blameable faculty or power of a man.',86,1586,'ROOT'),(755,'$Eb','sh‘b','','','شعب','شعب',2,'To separate, collect, appear, scatter, repair, impair, send (a message to), branch off. shu\'ub (pl. of sha\'bun) - large tribe, nation, collection. shu\'abin (pl. of shu\'batun) - twigs or branches of a tree, space between two branches, portion. Shu\'ayb - name of a prophet sent to the Midianites.\r\n',86,1590,'ROOT'),(756,'$Er','sh‘r','','','شعر','شعر',40,'To know/perceive/understand, to acquaint, perceive by senses.\r\nMake verses, remark, poetry, poet, verse, art of poetry, feeling, knowledge.\r\nSirius, which was worshipped by the Arabs in Pagan times.\r\nMark/marker/signs/rites/symbols/observances/ceremonies/practices, the obligatory ordinances/statutes of God.\r\nA place where a thing is known to be.\r\nMeasure of length.\r\nSheep/goat.\r\nHair, innermost garment.\r\nTrees.\r\nA sign of people in war and in a journey, a call or cry by means of which to know another, banner.\r\nMash\'ar al-Haram - holy mosque in Muadhalifah (a place which lies between Makkah and Arafat, six miles from Kabah). The name Mash\'ar al-Haram is a compound of Mash\'ar meaning the place of perception or knowledge and Haram meaning sacred. Ash\'ara to make anyone understand, make known to.',86,1594,'ROOT'),(757,'$El','sh‘l','','','شعل','شعل',1,'To kindle, light (fire). ishta\'ala (vb. 8) - to be lighted, become shining and inflamed; ishta\'ala shayban - to become hoary, glisten with grey hairs.',87,1598,'ROOT'),(758,'$gf','shgf','','','شغف','شغف',1,'To affect deeply, affect in the heart\'s core, inspire (with violent love). Shaghfun - bottom of the heart, pericardium. Shaghaf - passionate love.',87,1601,'ROOT'),(759,'$gl','shgl','','','شغل','شغل',2,'To occupy, keep busy. Shughlun - occupation, work, employment.',87,1602,'ROOT'),(760,'$fE','shf‘','','','شفع','شفع',31,'To make even that which was odd, make double, pair, make a thing to be one of the pair, adjoin a thing to its like, provide a thing which was alone with another, protect, mediate, intercede, be an intercessor. Shaf\'un - pair, double. shafa\'at - likeness/similarity, intercede or pray for a person.',87,1606,'ROOT'),(761,'$fq','shfq','shfq','','شفق','شفق',11,'To pity, be anxious about, fear. Shafaq - fear, pity, evening, twilight with its redness or whiteness, after sunset. Ashfaqa - to be afraid. Mushfiqun - one who is afraid or is in terror, compassionate, fearful one, tender.',87,1608,'ROOT'),(762,'$fh','shfh','shfh','','شفه','شفه',1,'To strike on the lips, lip.',87,1609,'ROOT'),(763,'$fw','shfw','shfw','','شفو','شفو',2,'To be at the point of, near its setting (sun), appear (new moon), extremity, brink, remainder of life, light.',87,1609,'ROOT'),(764,'$fy','shfy','','','شفي','شفي',6,'To cure, quench, restore to health. Shifa - recovery, remedy, healing.',87,1610,'ROOT'),(765,'$qq','shqq','','','شقق','شقق',28,'Pass along the way, cross, open a way/passage/vent/channel, cut/split/divided/clave/ripped/tore.',87,1610,'ROOT'),(766,'$qw','shqw','','','شقو','شقو',12,'To be miserable, be wretched, in distress, be unhappy, unblessed, disappointed. Ashqaa - most wretched.',87,1616,'ROOT'),(767,'$kr','shkr','','','شكر','شكر',75,'To give thanks, be grateful, realize or acknowledge one\'s favour, praise. Shukrun - giving thanks, gratitude. Shaakirun - one who gives thanks or is grateful, appreciated and bountiful in reward. Shakruurun - thankful. Sometimes a distinction is made between this word and shaakirun. The former is used to denote a person who is thankful for little or for nothing, the latter grateful for large favours. Mashkuurun - gratefully accepted, acceptable.\r\n',87,1619,'ROOT'),(768,'$ks','shks','','','شكس','شكس',1,'To be perverse, stubborn, cross-tempered. Tashaakasa - to wrangle, quarrel. Mutashakisun - quarreling, at variance with each other.\r\n',88,1620,'ROOT'),(769,'$kk','shkk','','','شكك','شكك',15,'To doubt.',87,1617,'ROOT'),(770,'$kl','shkl','','','شكل','شكل',2,'To mark, fashion, shackle. Shakilatun - likeness, mode, way, manner, disposition, rule of conduct, fashion, peculiar manner. Shakl - similitude/likeness',88,1621,'ROOT'),(771,'$kw','shkw','','','شكو','شكو',3,'To complain/accuse, bewail. Ashka - to listen to the complaint, remove the cause of complaint, satisfy the complaint of anyone by. Shakwatun - small water-skin, pillar on which a lamp is put. Ishtakaa - to make a complaint. Mishkaat - niche for a lamp in the wall, pillar on which a lamp is put.',88,1624,'ROOT'),(772,'$mt','shmt','','','شمت','شمت',1,'To rejoice at another\'s evil.',88,1629,'ROOT'),(773,'$mx','shmx','shmkh','','شمخ','شمخ',1,'To be high and lofty, tall.',88,1631,'ROOT'),(774,'$mz','shmz','','','شمز','شمز',1,'To feel aversion for, be seized with horror, feel disgust at, loathe a thing. Ishma\'azza - to shrink from, shrink with aversion, creep or contract with horror.',88,1631,'ROOT'),(775,'$ms','shms','','','شمس','شمس',33,'To be bright with sunshine, be glorious, be sunny. Shams - sun.',88,1631,'ROOT'),(776,'$ml','shml','','','شمل','شمل',12,'To include, contain, conceive, comprise, comprehend. Shimaal (pl. shamaa\'il) - left, north.',88,1634,'ROOT'),(777,'$nA','shn\'','','','شنا','شنا',3,'To hate/loathe. Shanaanan - hatred, insult, adversity, enmity, hostility, malice, abhorring. Shaaniun - insulter, enemy, foe, adversary, antagonist. Shaan\'ka - your enemy.\r\n',88,1640,'ROOT'),(778,'$hb','shhb','','','شهب','شهب',5,'To burn/scorch, become of a colour in which whiteness predominates over blackness. Shihaab (pl. shuhub) - flaming fire, bright blaze/meteor, star, penetrating flame, shining star, brisk/sprightly, flame, brand, radiating or gleaming fire, shooting or falling star. shihaab al-herb - dauntless warrior, one who is penetrating sharp and energetic in war.',88,1643,'ROOT'),(779,'$hd','shhd','','','شهد','شهد',160,'Told/gave information, to witness/see, to be present, give evidence/testimony, bear witness. Mushhad - time or place of being present or of giving or hearing evidence, meeting place. Mashhuud - that which is witnessed.',88,1644,'ROOT'),(780,'$hr','shhr','','','شهر','شهر',21,'Make it notable/known/manifest/public/infamous (in a bad or good sense), hire/contract for a month, stay a month, month old, month, new moon, moon, full moon, any evil thing that exposes its author to disgrace, a vice/fault or the like, big & bulky, reputable/eminent.',89,1647,'ROOT'),(781,'$hq','shhq','','','شهق','شهق',2,'To draw in the breath while sighing, sigh, roaring.',89,1648,'ROOT'),(782,'$hw','shhw','','','شهو','شهو',13,'To desire, wish, covet, crave; to make covetous, fill with desire, allure; lust; arouse greed, desire, appetite; to be appetising (food); to be covetous, greedy, lustful.',89,1649,'ROOT'),(783,'$wb','shwb','','','شوب','شوب',1,'To mingle/mix, he adulterated/sophisticated it, to confound/confuse. Shawb - mixture for drink.',89,1650,'ROOT'),(784,'$wr','shwr','','','شور','شور',4,'Gather, extract, exhibit, show, display, examine, consult, debate, counsel, advice, make known, notify, command, order, enjoin.',89,1651,'ROOT'),(785,'$wZ','shwẓ','','','شوظ','شوظ',1,'To abuse, use abusive language, brawl, hurl abuses. shuwaazun - smokeless blaze, flame, smoke, intenseness of fire/heat, heat of sun, vehement burning/thirst, thirst for revenge, scream/shriek/screech.',89,1654,'ROOT'),(786,'$wk','shwk','','','شوك','شوك',1,'To prick, be sharp-pointed, thorn, show vigour. Shaukatun - weapon, power, might, spur.',89,1655,'ROOT'),(787,'$wy','shwy','','','شوي','شوي',2,'To roast/scald/grill. Shawan - scalp, skin of head, skin even to the extremities (of the body).',89,1659,'ROOT'),(788,'$yA','shy\'','','','شيا','شيا',519,'To will/wish. Shaiun (pl. ashyaa\'un) - thing/matter, affair in any way, at all, what is willed or wished, aught, any extent. In direct objective case it is often used to denote the meaning \"a little\", \"bit\", \"at all\". Adverbially it means \"in any way\", \"at all\".',89,1660,'ROOT'),(789,'$yb','shyb','','','شيب','شيب',3,'To be hoary (hair), to grow old, go grey.',89,1662,'ROOT'),(790,'$yx','shyx','shykh','','شيخ','شيخ',4,'To be old, old/aged man.',90,1663,'ROOT'),(791,'$yd','shyd','','','شيد','شيد',2,'To plaster or coat (a wall), raise (a building), lofty, fortify.',90,1664,'ROOT'),(792,'$yE','shy‘','','','شيع','شيع',12,'Become spread/published/known/revealed/apparent, scattered/dispersed, conforming/agreeing with another, befriend/friendly, went along together, like/similar, follower/assistant/friend/comrade/sharer/partner, separate/distinct party/sect, way of doctrine/system/practice.',90,1666,'ROOT'),(793,'SbA','ṣb\'','','','صبا','صبا',3,'To change one\'s religion, lead (a troop), rise (star), touch, wish. Saabii (pl. saabiuun) - the word refers to certain religious sects that were found in parts of Arabia and countries bordering it.',90,1675,'ROOT'),(794,'Sbb','ṣbb','','','صبب','صبب',5,'To pour out, be poured out. \r\nsabbun - the act of pouring. \r\nsabban - the act of pouring heavily.',90,1673,'ROOT'),(795,'SbH','ṣbḥ','','','صبح','صبح',45,'To visit or greet in the morning. \r\nsubhun/sabahun/isbaahun - the morning. \r\nmisbaahun (pl. masaabih) - lamp. \r\nsabbah (vb. 2) - to come to, come upon, greet, drink in the morning. \r\nasbaha - to enter upon the time of the morning, appear, begin to do, to be, become, happen. \r\nmusbih - one who does anything in or enters upon the morning.',90,1675,'ROOT'),(796,'Sbr','ṣbr','','','صبر','صبر',103,'To bind, be patient or constant, endure patiently, steadily adhere to reason and command, restrain from what reason and law forbid, restrain from manifesting grief, agitation and impatience. The word being the contrary of jaz\'a (manifestation of grief and agitation).',90,1678,'ROOT'),(797,'SbE','ṣb‘','','','صبع','صبع',2,'To point out with the finger. \r\nasaabi - finger.',90,1681,'ROOT'),(798,'Sbg','ṣbg','','','صبغ','صبغ',3,'To dye, colour, baptize, dip, immerse, hue, assume the attribute, mode, mature, code of law, religion, nature.',90,1682,'ROOT'),(799,'Sbw','ṣbw','','','صبو','صبو',3,'To be inclined, yearn, long for, have child-like propensities, feel a youthful propensity. \r\nsabiyyan - boy/lad/male, child, young boy.\r\n',91,1684,'ROOT'),(800,'SHb','ṣḥb','','','صحب','صحب',97,'To accompany, associate, be the friend of or companion to. \r\nsaahibun (pl. sahbuun and ashaabun) - companion, associate, possessor of any quality or thing, one in an intimate relation with anything, fellow and showing any type of connection or link, helper. \r\nsaahibatun - spouse, consort, wife. \r\nsaahaba - to bear company. \r\nashaba (vb. 4) -to preserve, hinder, keep from, defend from. \r\nyushabuun - they will be accompanied.',91,1687,'ROOT'),(801,'SHf','ṣḥf','','','صحف','صحف',9,'To write or read, dig. \r\nsahfatun (pl. sihaaf) - hollow, large dish. \r\nsahiifa - surface of the earth. \r\nsahiifatun (pl. suhuf) - heap of a book.',91,1689,'ROOT'),(802,'Sxx','ṣxx','Skhkh','ṣkhkh','صخخ','صخخ',1,'To strike sound on the ear, strike (iron) upon (stones), deafen (the ears, noise), accuse (of great crime). \r\nsakhkhah - deafening cry/shout/noise.',91,1692,'ROOT'),(803,'Sxr','ṣxr','Skhr','ṣkhr','صخر','صخر',3,'To be rocky (place). \r\nsakhr - rock',91,1693,'ROOT'),(804,'Sdd','ṣdd','','','صدد','صدد',42,'To turn away, divert, hinder, avert. \r\nsadiidan - to shun a thing, shrink from, raise, clamour, shout, cry aloud. saddun - the act of hindering, diverting or turning away. \r\nsadiid - anything that is repulsive, hot or boiling water.',91,1693,'ROOT'),(805,'Sdr','ṣdr','','','صدر','صدر',46,'To return from, come back, proceed, issue or emanate from, go forward, advance or promote, come to pass, happen, emanate from, strike on the chest/breast, commence. Anything that fronts, or faces one; hence breast, chest or bosom [often meaning his mind]. The fore part of anything. Going, or turning back and away.\r\nsadr - heart/breast/chest, mind, prominent place.',91,1695,'ROOT'),(806,'SdE','ṣd‘','','','صدع','صدع',5,'To split, expound, cleave, profess openly, divide, cross, proclaim, promulgate aloud, declare openly, be affected with headache, manifest, make clear. \r\nsad\'un - fissure. suddi\'a - to oppress with or suffer from headache. \r\nissada\'a (vb. 5) - to be split up or divided. mutasaddiun - that which is cloven or splits in two.',91,1698,'ROOT'),(807,'Sdf','ṣdf','','','صدف','صدف',5,'To turn away, shun aside, hinder, prevent, bar, prohibit. \r\nsadaf - barrier, obstacle, obstruction, hindrance, restriction, prevention, interruption, limitation, prohibition, check, steep side of a mountain.',91,1700,'ROOT'),(808,'Sdq','ṣdq','','','صدق','صدق',155,'To be truthful, true, sincere, speak the truth, establish or confirm the truth of what another has said, verify, keep faith, observe a promise faithfully, fulfill, speak veraciously, hold anyone as trustworthy. \r\nsadaqa fi al-qitaali - to fight gallantly. tsaddaqa - to give alms. \r\nsidqun - truth, veracity, sincerity, soundness, excellence in a variety of different objects, salubrious and agreeable, favourable entrance, praise. \r\nsaadiqun - one who is true and sincere, one who speaks the truth. \r\nsaadiqah - perfect woman. \r\nsadaqat (pl. saduqaat) - dowry. \r\nsiddiiq - person who is trustworthy, sincere. \r\nsaddaqa - to confirm, verify, fulfil. \r\nasdaqu - more true.',91,1701,'ROOT'),(809,'Sdy','ṣdy','','','صدي','صدي',2,'To clap the hands, receive with honour, applaud, pay attention, address, direct one\'s regard or attention or mind, incline.',92,1705,'ROOT'),(810,'SrH','ṣrḥ','','','صرح','صرح',4,'To make manifest, explain, clarify. \r\nsarhun - palace, high tower, lofty structure, castle.',92,1710,'ROOT'),(811,'Srx','ṣrx','Srkh','ṣrkh','صرخ','صرخ',5,'To cry out loudly, cry/implore for help/assistance, shout for succour.',92,1711,'ROOT'),(812,'Srr','ṣrr','','','صرر','صرر',6,'To resolve, persist, persevere in. \r\nasarra (vb. 4) - to be obstinate, persist obstinately. \r\nasarruu - they persisted. \r\nsirrun - intense cold. \r\nsarratin - moaning, vociferating.',92,1706,'ROOT'),(813,'SrSr','ṣrṣr','','','صرصر','صرصر',3,'This is a quadrilateral verb derived from \r\nsarra - to cry out, make a chattering noise (as a green woodpecker). \r\nsarsarun - loud roaring and furious wind, blast of cold, wind, vehement wind, raging furious and intense cold (wind).',92,1713,'ROOT'),(814,'SrT','ṣrṭ','','','صرط','صرط',45,'A path which is even, wide enough and can be trodden without difficulty. A road/way/path, long sword.',92,1713,'ROOT'),(815,'SrE','ṣr‘','','','صرع','صرع',1,'To stick down, prostrate, fling. \r\nsar\'aa - lying or thrown prostrate, fallen down.',92,1713,'ROOT'),(816,'Srf','ṣrf','','','صرف','صرف',30,'To turn away, divert, avert, propound, set forth, vary. \r\nsarfun - act of averting. \r\nmasrifun - place to turn to, refuge. \r\nmasruufun - averted. \r\nsarrafa (vb. 2) - to explain. \r\ntasrif - change (of wind). \r\ninsarafa (vb. 7) - to turn aside.